# Phase 11: Subscriptions & Comments

## Goal Description
Implement a robust subscription system allowing users to follow channels and see a dedicated feed. Also refine the commenting experience with delete functionality and better component structure.

## Proposed Changes

### Database Schema
#### [NEW] [setup-subscriptions.sql](file:///C:/GoLive/setup-subscriptions.sql)
- Create `subscriptions` table (subscriber_id, channel_id, created_at).
- Add RLS policies (public read, auth insert/delete).

### Component Updates
#### [NEW] [components/CommentSection.tsx](file:///C:/GoLive/components/CommentSection.tsx)
- Extract comment logic from WatchPage.
- Add "Delete Comment" functionality.

#### [MODIFY] [app/watch/[id]/page.tsx](file:///C:/GoLive/app/watch/[id]/page.tsx)
- Replace inline comments with `CommentSection`.
- Implement functional Subscribe button (toggle state).

#### [MODIFY] [app/profile/[username]/page.tsx](file:///C:/GoLive/app/profile/[username]/page.tsx)
- Implement functional Subscribe button.

### New Pages
#### [NEW] [app/subscriptions/page.tsx](file:///C:/GoLive/app/subscriptions/page.tsx)
- Feed of videos from channels the user is subscribed to.
- Sorted by newest first.

## Verification Plan
### Manual Verification
- **Subscribe**: Click subscribe on a channel, verify button state changes.
- **Feed**: Go to `/subscriptions`, verify the channel's videos appear there.
- **Unsubscribe**: Click unsubscribe, verify video disappears from feed (on refresh).
- **Comments**: Post a comment, then delete it.
